description:
The Database Technician (DBT) must be skilled with data entry, data quality control, database management, data development, and SQL language. They must demonstrate an ability to work with development teams to assist with the Quality Assurance of application development, testing, and migration into production services. Working with local users and department teams, the DBT supports applications within the life cycle of the product providing technical support to staff with standard business operations to upload, manage and access their data stored in these systems.
 
This position offers the opportunity to work remotely with the occasional need to travel to the Central office for in person meetings.
 
Basic operation of Oracle and/or other SQL based database systems including upgrading, patching, installation and configuration, and backup and recovery operations. Basic operation of WebLogic and/or Tomcat application servers including upgrading, patching, installation and configuration, and application deployments
Provide support to end users as needed with database issues, troubleshooting and special configurations in response to the ERP development team and DBA.
Application upgrades and reconfiguration based on application life cycle and product requirements.  Cloning and deployment of alternative databases for testing, non-production and release quality assurance.
Documentation of changes to the ERP application environment, Database server configurations, application server configuration, and connected third party application configurations.
Quality assurance for new releases and packaging of application-specific patches, upgrades and bolt-on procedures applied to the ERP and other third party applications
Shell programming to automate existing processes, procedures or functions related to the ERP and/or third party applications
Perform other tasks as assigned
A self-starter who can work with a minimum amount of supervision;
Demonstrated organizational and project management skills;
Demonstrated ability to understand customer needs and provide quality service;
Demonstrated willingness to work flexible hours and rotate as an “on-call” troubleshooter;
Excellent interpersonal and oral/written communication skills;
A willingness and passion to learn new hardware/software systems that is consistent with duties;
Understands responsibilities with respect to conflicts of interest and behaves in ways consistent both with law and with institution policy;
Contributes toward creating a positive and respectful workplace defined by personal and professional competence, integrity, and collaboration;
Understands and contributes to implementation of departmental and institutional goals for achieving non-discrimination and creating a respectful, inclusive environment that is supportive of diversity;
Uses access to sensitive and/or not yet public institution related information only in the performance of the responsibilities of position and exercises care to prevent unnecessary disclosure to others
Associate’s degree in a relevant discipline with 2 – 3 years of job related experience preferred, or equivalent combination of education and/or experience;
Basic operation of Oracle and/or other SQL based database systems;
Experience with basic server administration and technical support of Solaris/Linux and Microsoft;
Working in a mixed hardware environment (Sun and Intel based hardware preferred);
Shell programming expertise with automating processes
Experience working in higher education environment

